    <manvolnum>8</manvolnum>
  </refmeta>

  <refnamediv>
    <refname>systemd-newmemory-auto-online.service</refname>
    <refname>systemd-newmemory-auto-online</refname>
    <refpurpose>Enable and disable automatic onlining for the newly added memory.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <para><filename>systemd-newmemory-auto-online.service</filename></para>
    <para><filename>/usr/lib/systemd/systemd-newmemory-auto-online</filename></para>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para><filename>systemd-newmemory-auto-online.service</filename>
    is a service that enables and disables automatic onlining for all newly
    added memory blocks. When the service is disabled all newly added memory
    stays in 'offline' state until someone enables it through the
    <filename>/sys/devices/system/memory/memory*/state</filename> interface.
    This service enables automatic onlining through the
    <filename>/sys/devices/system/memory/auto_online_blocks</filename>
    interface. This is particularly important for virtual machines where memory
    hotplug is used to address high memory pressure.
    </para>
  </refsect1>

